A total of 455 diterpenoids were isolated from the 

Euphorbia

genus between 2013 and 2019, and many of them showed significant biological activities, such as anticancer (

), anti-HIV (

) and anti-inflammatory activity (

). In this review, we summarize the structures and biological activities of the previously undescribed diterpenoids isolated from plants of the 

Euphorbia

genus from 2013 to 2019. The purpose of this review is to provide a reference for the further research and development of natural diterpenoids as drugs.

