Euphorkanlide A ( 451 ), a highly modified ingenane diterpenoid, showed significant cytotoxicities against a panel of cancer cell lines (IC 50 < 5 μM) (
). Three abietane diterpenoids (
3 – 5
) showed selective inhibitory potency against certain human tumor cell lines with IC 50 values ranging from 8.50 ± 0.13 to 35.52 ± 0.08 μM (
). Three diterpenoids, tigliane ( 407 ), ingenane ( 181 ) and abietane ( 36 ), were tested for their cytotoxicity against five cancer cell lines (A549, MCF-7, HepG2, HeLa and P388), with IC 50 values in the range 6.64–42.86 μM (
). A lathyrane-type diterpenoid ( 321 ) showed strong cytotoxicity to 786-O human kidney cells and HepG2 liver cancer cells, with IC 50 value of 9.43 μM and 13.22 μM, respectively (
). An ent -abietane-type diterpenoid ( 37 ) showed cytotoxicity against the two cell lines with IC 50 values of 19.5 μM (NCI–H460) and 18.6 μM (MCF-7), while for cis -platinum (a positive control) exhibiting IC 50 values of 29.7 μM (NCI–H460) and 27.7 μM (MCF-7). A rosane-type diterpenoid ( 150 ) showed weak inhibition of tumor growth with an IC 50 value of 14.90 ± 2.01 μg (
). An ingenane ( 178 ) showed significant cytotoxicity against A549 with an IC 50 value of 3.35 μg/mL (
). Two norlathyrane diterpenoids, ekanpenoids A and B, exhibited potent cytotoxic activities against the HeLa and Hep-G2 cell lines with IC 50 values ranging from 3.6 to 9.7 μM (
). A cembrane diterpenoid, ()-(1 S )-15-hydroxy-18-carboxycembrene ( 156 ), showed cytotoxic activity against five human cancer cell lines including HeLa, PC-3, HT1080, A375-S2 and MDA231, with IC 50 values of 35.3 ± 3.6, 53.9 ± 6.2, 37.3 ± 2.0, 28.7 ± 3.8 and 43.5 ± 5.1 μM, respectively (
). Euphordraculoates B ( 453 ), which possesses a novel carbon skeleton, showed cytotoxic activities on all the tested cells, Caco2, HT29, and HCT116, with IC 50 values of 10.97, 31.78, and 42.58 μM, respectively (
). A tigliane-type diterpenoid ester, 4, 20-dideoxy-4 α -phorbol-12 β -acetate-13 α -isobutyrate ( 405 ), exhibited weak cytotoxic effects against promyelocytic leukemia HL60 cells, with IC 50 values of 97 μM (
). An ingenane-type diterpenoid ( 180 ) was found to be cytotoxic against A375 and HMCB cells with IC 50 values of 15.37 ± 2.6 μM and 15.62 ± 1.89 μM, respectively (
). A rosane-type diterpenoid ( 154 ) exhibited moderate cytotoxic effects against HL-60, A549, SMMC-7721, MCF-7, and SW480 with IC 50 values of 17.5, 11.0, 16.8, 17.5, and 18.0 μM (
), respectively. Euphorikanin A ( 447 ), an unprecedented diterpenoid lactone possessing a 5/6/7/3-fused tetracyclic ring skeleton, exhibited moderate cytotoxicity against two human tumor cell lines HeLa and NCI-446 (
). An ent -atisane-type diterpenoid ( 78 ) showed significant inhibitory activity on human breast cancer MCF-7 cells with IC 50 values of 10.0 μM (
). Two ent -atisanes, 80 and 81 , showed inhibitory effects against MCF-7 cells with IC 50 values of 23.21 and 15.42 μM (
). Two myrsinol-type diterpenoids (
371 – 372
) exhibited moderate inhibitory effects, with IC 50 values of 24.53 ± 3.39 and 26.67 ± 1.41 μM against MDA-MB cell line, and 37.73 ± 3.41 and 34.57 ± 2.12 μM against MCF-7 cell line, respectively (
). An ent -isopimarane-type diterpenoid ( 115 ) showed cytotoxic activity against the A549 cancer cell line with an IC 50 value of 13.033 μg/mL (
).

Two ingenane-type diterpenoids (
168 – 169
) exhibited potent activities against HIV-1, with IC 50 values of 2.7 ± 1.3 and 1.1 ± 0.3 nM, respectively (
). Two abietane type diterpenoids (
33 – 34
) exhibited significant anti-HIV activities, with EC 50 values of 3.58 ± 0.31 μM (SI = 8.6) and 7.40 ± 0.94 μM (SI = 10.3), respectively (
). Compound 431 showed activity against HIV-1 replication with an IC 50 value of 1.76 ± 0.61 μM (
). A diterpenoid ( 411 ) showed activity against HIV-1 replication, with IC 50 and SI values of 28.6 ± 0.8 μM and 86.1, respectively (
). An atisane ( 77 ) showed moderate anti-HIV-1 activities, with EC 50 values of 34 μM (SI = 2.3) (
). Lower diterpenoids show much better anti-HIV-1 activity than higher diterpenoids. Two ingenane-type diterpenoids (
174 – 175
), showed moderate activity against RSV virus, both with IC 50 values of 25 μM and selective indices of 1.0 and 3.2, respectively (
). An ent- atisane-type diterpenoid ( 86 ) showed antiviral activities against human rhinovirus 3, with an IC 50 value of 90.35 μM (
). A rosane-type diterpenoid ( 132 ) showed significant potent inhibitory activity on EBV with an EC 50 value of 5.4 μM similar to the positive control ( + )-rutamarin (EC 50 = 5.4 μM) (
).

