A rosane type diterpenoid ( 151 ) showed an inhibitory effect against the target enzyme GlmU, with a moderate inhibitory effect with an IC 50 value of 12.5 μg/mL, which displayed an antituberculosis effect (
). Myrsinol-type diterpenoids 367 had strong antifungal activity against the fungus
Physalospora piricola
with an EC 50 value of 28.26 μg/mL (
). Therefore, it seems that the antibacterial activity of myrsinane-type skeletons with few free hydroxyl groups is better.

A jatrophane diterpenoid ( 230 ) strongly inhibited the drug-efflux activity of the primary ABC transporter CaCdr1p with an IC 50 value of 31.7 ± 2.9 (
). Two jatrophane-type diterpenoids (
241 – 242
